  Understand this as a Human body-
  Nervous system-MotherBoard
  Brain-cpu(Cental processing unit)/Processors 
  short term memory-RAM(Random access memory)also called Volatile
  Long term memory-HDD/SSD(Hard disk or solid state drive)called as Non volatle
will ce what is volatile or non volatile but before first lets understand how each things work.

Motherboard:
# Motherboard is a printed circuit board where Cpu is placed inside which acts as a brain for every pc and laptops that we
use nowadys,also processors which is a harware chip which contains multiple cores of CPU so called as Multi-core processors basically contains
4 CPUs(Quad-core).The core that acutally performs compuatation and instruction execution.
# When u see in any laptop there will be a stiker near keypad and that is non other than processors company name and if u 
knew, then Congrats!.
CPU:
  Basic funtions of CPUs are- 
  *ALU(Arthmetic Logic unit) - Performs calculations and logic comparison
  *CU(Contol unit) - directs the operation like a Manger
  *Registers - Small, Super-fast memory locations like scartcpad.
Simple Analogy

Imagine a chef in a kitchen ðŸ³:
->The recipe book = Memory (RAM)
->The chef = CPU
->The chef reads a recipe (fetches)
->Understands the steps (decodes)
->Cooks the dish (executes)
->Then moves on to the next recipe.

RAM is very well known by u gys,yes its a short term memory location does not store your OS or files permanently.
HDD/SSD - Its the main storage component which stores your data permanently even when you shutdown,amazingly it stores 2 Terabytes of storages
which is more sufficient for normal uses like me.
